CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 4, 1961, pg. 34, reads: "Unbeaten Fifth Ave. High Five - Riding the crest of a perfect first half, with seven triumphs in as many starts, Coach George Cupples and his brilliant starters pose in above picture for The Courier photographer. From left: Andy Walton, Ulysses Winn, Charles Franklin, Coach Cupples and Captain John Wilkins.  The mentor has expressed a personal hope that his hoopsters may capture the city high school basketball title."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Fifth Avenue High School basketball team, including from left: #30 Andy Walton, #21 Ulysses Winn, #42 Charles Franklin, Coach George Cupples holding basketball, and John Wilkins #40 or #23, posed under basket in gymnasium
